cdx6500PPCT3201PortTable.description: This table contains the 3201 Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500PPCT3201PortEntry.description: Entries in the 3201 Port Configuration Table.

iso3201PCfgPortType.name: iso3201PCfgPortType
iso3201PCfgPortType.description: The Port Type of the port.

iso3201PCfgPortSpeed.name: iso3201PCfgPortSpeed
iso3201PCfgPortSpeed.description: This specifies port speed in bits per second speed300 : 300 bits per second speed600 : 600 bits per second speed1200 : 1200 bits per second speed1800 : 1800 bits per second speed2400 : 2400 bits per second speed4800 : 4800 bits per second speed7200 : 7200 bits per second speed9600 : 9600 bits per second speed19200 : 19200 bits per second .

iso3201PCfgNoOfControllers.name: iso3201PCfgNoOfControllers
iso3201PCfgNoOfControllers.description: This specifies the number of controllers on this line.

iso3201PCfgResponseTimeout.name: iso3201PCfgResponseTimeout
iso3201PCfgResponseTimeout.description: This specifies the amount of time in 1/20th of a second that the PAD waits for a response from a controller. A value of 5 gives a response timeout of 250ms.

iso3201PCfgInterChrTimeout.name: iso3201PCfgInterChrTimeout
iso3201PCfgInterChrTimeout.description: This specifies the maximum amount of time in 1/20 of a second that the PAD waits between two characters when receiving data from the attatched devices before detecting a line problem. A value of 2 gives an intercharacter timeout of 100ms.

iso3201PCfgNoOfRetries.name: iso3201PCfgNoOfRetries
iso3201PCfgNoOfRetries.description: This specifies the retry limit for polls/selects sent, NAKs sent/received and ENQs sent/received. In case of polls and selects, the controller is placed in slow poll mode on reaching this limit.

iso3201PCfgNoOfConsecRetries.name: iso3201PCfgNoOfConsecRetries
iso3201PCfgNoOfConsecRetries.description: This specifies the number of retries that will be made immediately in case of response timeout on Poll, response timeout on Select or NAK response to select. The next controller in the list will be polled/selected only after these many retries are made for the non-responding controller. All consecutive retries will be counted as one retry attempt.

iso3201PCfgSlowPollWaitCycle.name: iso3201PCfgSlowPollWaitCycle
iso3201PCfgSlowPollWaitCycle.description: This specifies the number of poll cycles to active controllers before a poll is sent to one controller in the slow poll list.

iso3201PCfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: iso3201PCfgElectricalInterfaceType
iso3201PCfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

iso3201PCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.name: iso3201PCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
iso3201PCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

iso3201PCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceO.name: iso3201PCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
iso3201PCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceO.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500SPCT3201StnTable.name: cdx6500SPCT3201StnTable
cdx6500SPCT3201StnTable.description: This table contains the 3201 Station Configuration parameters.

cdx6500SPCT3201StnEntry.description: Entries in the 3201 Station Configuration Table.

iso3201SCfgControllerAddress.name: iso3201SCfgControllerAddress
iso3201SCfgControllerAddress.description: This specifies the address of this controller The valid addresses are : 0x20, 0x21, 0x22, 0x23, 0x24, 0x25, 0x26, 0x27, 0x28, 0x29, 0x2A, 0x2B, 0x2C, 0x2D, 0x2E, 0x2F, 0x40, 0x41, 0x42, 0x43, 0x44, 0x45, 0x46, 0x47, 0x48, 0x49, 0x4A, 0x4B, 0x4C, 0x4D, 0x4E, 0x4F, 0x60, 0x61, 0x62, 0x63, 0x64, 0x65, 0x66, 0x67, 0x68, 0x69, 0x6A, 0x6B, 0x6C, 0x6D, 0x6E, 0x6F.

iso3201SCfgAutocallMnemonic.name: iso3201SCfgAutocallMnemonic
iso3201SCfgAutocallMnemonic.description: This specifies the mnemonic used by the PAD to place calls to the Host for this controller. Host initiated calls will be accepted only if this field is blank.

iso3201SCfgAutocallTimeout.name: iso3201SCfgAutocallTimeout
iso3201SCfgAutocallTimeout.description: This specifies the time interval in seconds between call attempts.

iso3201SCfgMaxNoAutocallAttempts.name: iso3201SCfgMaxNoAutocallAttempts
iso3201SCfgMaxNoAutocallAttempts.description: This specifies the number of times autocall attempts will be made. A value of 0 will allow unlimited attempts.

iso3201SCfgX25Address.name: iso3201SCfgX25Address
iso3201SCfgX25Address.description: This specifies the X.25 address inserted in the calling address field of the call packet sent by the PAD to the Host. This address identifies the controller to the Host.

iso3201SCfgBillingRecords.name: iso3201SCfgBillingRecords
iso3201SCfgBillingRecords.description: This controls whether billing(accounting) records will be created for calls on this station billingDisabled : billing is disabled billingEnabled : billing is enabled .

iso3201PStatsLineStatus.description: This indicates the line status : up : if one or more controllers are responding to polls down : if no controllers are responding or garbage is being received.

iso3201PStatsTxNAKs.description: This specifies the number of messages for which NAKs were transmitted.

iso3201PStatsTxENQs.name: iso3201PStatsTxENQs

iso3201PStatsRxChrs.name: iso3201PStatsRxChrs
iso3201PStatsRxChrs.description: This specifies the number of characters received.

iso3201PStatsRxMsgs.name: iso3201PStatsRxMsgs

cdx6500SPST3201SStatsTable.description: This table contains 3201 Station statistics parameters.

cdx6500SPST3201StnEntry.name: cdx6500SPST3201StnEntry
cdx6500SPST3201StnEntry.description: Entries in the 3201 Station statistics table.

iso3201SStatsControllerAddress.name: iso3201SStatsControllerAddress
iso3201SStatsControllerAddress.description: This specifies the address of this controller The valid addresses are : 0x20, 0x21, 0x22, 0x23, 0x24, 0x25, 0x26, 0x27, 0x28, 0x29, 0x2A, 0x2B, 0x2C, 0x2D, 0x2E, 0x2F, 0x40, 0x41, 0x42, 0x43, 0x44, 0x45, 0x46, 0x47, 0x48, 0x49, 0x4A, 0x4B, 0x4C, 0x4D, 0x4E, 0x4F, 0x60, 0x61, 0x62, 0x63, 0x64, 0x65, 0x66, 0x67, 0x68, 0x69, 0x6A, 0x6B, 0x6C, 0x6D, 0x6E, 0x6F.

iso3201SStatsStnState.name: iso3201SStatsStnState
iso3201SStatsStnState.description: This indicates the current state of the station up : when responding to polls down : when tries have expired and controller is in slow poll suspended : when polling has been stopped by host blocked : when polling has been stopped because the X.25 channel is blocked disabled : when station is disabled.

iso3201SStatsCurrentStatus.name: iso3201SStatsCurrentStatus
iso3201SStatsCurrentStatus.description: This gives information regarding the calls placed by this station on its host. calling : when it is waiting call accept from the host connected : when the connection to the host has been accepted idle : when connection attempts are not in progress (no data to send to the Host), or autocall attempts have been exhausted or when it is waiting for autocall timeout (to send call request again).

iso3201SStatsNoOfAutocallAttmpts.name: iso3201SStatsNoOfAutocallAttmpts
iso3201SStatsNoOfAutocallAttmpts.description: This indicates the number of attempts made to establish connection to the host. This is reset to 0 when a connection is established.

iso3201SStatsNxtAutocallAttmpt.name: iso3201SStatsNxtAutocallAttmpt
iso3201SStatsNxtAutocallAttmpt.description: This indicates the time (in seconds ) after which the station will place autocall to the host.

iso3201SStatsLastInCalledAddress.name: iso3201SStatsLastInCalledAddress
iso3201SStatsLastInCalledAddress.description: This indicates the called address in the last inbound call request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the last incoming call packet is not present.

iso3201SStatsLastInCallingAddress.name: iso3201SStatsLastInCallingAddress
iso3201SStatsLastInCallingAddress.description: This indicates the calling address in the last inbound request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the last incoming call packet is not present.

iso3201SStatsLastInCallFacilities.name: iso3201SStatsLastInCallFacilities
iso3201SStatsLastInCallFacilities.description: This indicates the facilities in the last inbound request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the last incoming call packet is not present.

iso3201SStatsLastInCallCUD.name: iso3201SStatsLastInCallCUD
iso3201SStatsLastInCallCUD.description: This indicates the data in the Call User Data field in the last inbound call request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the incoming call packet is not present.

iso3201SStatsLastOutCalledAddress.name: iso3201SStatsLastOutCalledAddress
iso3201SStatsLastOutCalledAddress.description: This indicates the called address in the last outbound call request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the last outgoing call packet is not present.

iso3201SStatsLastOutCallingAddress.name: iso3201SStatsLastOutCallingAddress
iso3201SStatsLastOutCallingAddress.description: This indicates the calling address in the last outbound call request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the last outgoing call packet is not present.

iso3201SStatsLastOutCallFacilities.name: iso3201SStatsLastOutCallFacilities
iso3201SStatsLastOutCallFacilities.description: This indicates the facilities in the last outbound call request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the last outgoing call packet is not present.

iso3201SStatsLastOutCallCUD.name: iso3201SStatsLastOutCallCUD
iso3201SStatsLastOutCallCUD.description: This indicates the data in the Call User Data field in the last outbound call request packet sent by this station. A value of 'Last Call Information not available' will be returned if the last call outgoing packet is not present.
